  "approach": "Monorepo with three packages: (1) SvelteKit app handling auth, resume CRUD, theme selection, live preview, and subdomain routing; (2) Rust microservice wrapping SRG for HTML-to-PDF conversion exposed via a simple HTTP API; (3) shared database migrations. SvelteKit handles both the marketing site (hosted-resumes.com) and the tenant subdomains (username.hosted-resumes.com) using SvelteKit hooks to detect the host header and route accordingly - no separate app needed. JOBL resumes are stored as JSONB in PostgreSQL alongside user/subscription metadata. Themes are server-rendered Svelte components that take JOBL data as props, producing both the live preview and the final hosted page. PDF export calls the Rust service with the rendered HTML. S3 stores profile photos and uploaded assets only. Wildcard DNS + a Caddy/nginx config handles subdomain routing to the same SvelteKit instance. Stripe handles subscriptions with webhook-driven tier enforcement.",
